cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with image-based control of ablation lasers in microsurgery using optical coherence tomography (OCT) as a high-resolution imaging modality. The paper presents a deep learning-based tracking scheme for concise representations of subsequent 3D OCT volumes. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses a self-supervised convolutional neural network for estimating the dense optical flow and depth changes for tracking distinctive subcutaneous structures on OCTs. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image-based control of ablation lasers in microsurgery using optical coherence tomography (OCT) as a high-resolution imaging modality. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper presents a deep learning-based tracking scheme for concise representations of subsequent 3D OCT volumes. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with automated control of ablation lasers in microsurgery using image-guidance, which is a common application in robotics.
